parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Activation of Automatic Parking Brake System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended activation of the automatic parking brake system can cause the vehicle to suddenly stop or lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The automatic parking brake system engages without warning
the vehicle suddenly stops or loses control
the brake lights do not illuminate when the parking brake engages
and the vehicle is unable to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electric auto brake system can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly when in park, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The auto park brake will not unlock at times
the auto park brake locks up while driving
the vehicle rolls or moves when in park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the actuator bar can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly when in park, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: the vehicle rolls or moves when in park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause multiple critical systems to malfunction, including the gauges, instrument panel lights, power steering, and brakes, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: instrument panel lights fail to illuminate
brake pedal travels to the floorboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the suspension can cause the vehicle to shake and lose steering power, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle stability.
